'''Jesper Kewe Karlström''' (born 21 June 1995) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Udinese}} club [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]], which he [[Captain (association football)|captains]], and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Karlström started out his career playing for [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] at the age of six. When he turned nine the coach of his team moved to [[IF Brommapojkarna]] and brought his entire youth team along with him to the new club, including Karlström.<ref>{{cite web|title=Djurgården kändes perfekt – jag velade ingenting|date=24 February 2015 |url=http://www.fotbolldirekt.se/2015/02/24/djurgardens-kandes-perfekt-jag-velade-ingenting/|publisher=FotbollDirekt|accessdate=26 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jesper Karlström|url=https://svenskfotboll.se/allsvenskan/person/?playerid=7619|publisher=svenskfotboll.se|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>

===IF Brommapojkarna===
Shortly after his eighteenth birthday in 2013, Karlström made his [[Allsvenskan]] debut for Brommapojkarna away against [[Kalmar FF]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jesper nöjd med debuten |url=http://brommapojkarna.se/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1274:jesper-noejd-med-debuten&catid=82:nyheter&Itemid=422 |publisher=[[IF Brommapojkarna]] |access-date=26 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226051715/http://brommapojkarna.se/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1274%3Ajesper-noejd-med-debuten&catid=82%3Anyheter&Itemid=422 |archive-date=26 February 2015 }}</ref> At the start of the next year he scored for the first time when his game-winning goal in the last game of the [[2013–14 Svenska Cupen]] group stage qualified the club for the knockout stage of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jespers första – BP cupvann |url=http://brommapojkarna.se/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1596:jespers-foersta-bp-cupvann&catid=82:nyheter&Itemid=422 |publisher=[[IF Brommapojkarna]] |access-date=26 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226052503/http://brommapojkarna.se/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1596%3Ajespers-foersta-bp-cupvann&catid=82%3Anyheter&Itemid=422 |archive-date=26 February 2015 }}</ref> A few months later he also scored his first league goal in the 3–0 home win against [[IFK Norrköping]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Stjärnskottet gav BP segern|work=Dagens Nyheter |date=3 May 2014|url=https://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/stjarnskottet-gav-bp-segern/|access-date=26 February 2015}}</ref>

===Djurgårdens IF===
Brommapojkarna were relegated at the end of the [[2014 Allsvenskan]] season, but Karlström had performed well enough to be signed by the larger [[Stockholm]] club [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] on a four-year deal.<ref name="dif">{{cite web|title=Jesper Karlström klar för DIF|url=http://dif.se/2015/01/22/jesper-karlstrom-klar-for-dif/|publisher=[[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]]|access-date=26 February 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20150124144029/http://dif.se/2015/01/22/jesper-karlstrom-klar-for-dif/|archive-date=24 January 2015}}</ref> Ahead of 2017 Karlström had his shirt number changed from 22 to 6. On 10 May 2018, he played as Djurgarden beat [[Malmö FF]] 3–0 in the [[2018 Svenska Cupen final]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://dif.se/djurgarden-cupmastare-malmo-kordes-over/ |title=DIF.se &#124; Djurgården cupmästare |access-date=11 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511145855/http://dif.se/djurgarden-cupmastare-malmo-kordes-over/ |archive-date=11 May 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

In 2019 Karlström crowned himself as a Swedish champion as part of the [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] team that won the Swedish league for a twelfth time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allsvenskan.se/nyheter/nyheter-fran-allsvenskan.se/djurgarden-svenska-mastare-2019|title = Djurgården Svenska Mästare 2019| date=2 November 2019 }}</ref> Karlström contributed with the 2–1 goal in the remarkable second-half comeback to win the title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/tv/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/klipp/har-tands-hoppet-for-djurgarden/|title = Här tänds hoppet för Djurgården| date=2 November 2019 }}</ref>

===Lech Poznań===
On 2 December 2020, [[Lech Poznań]] announced Karlström had signed from [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] on a contract until June 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lechpoznan.pl/aktualnosci,2,jesper-karlstrom-od-stycznia-pilkarzem-lecha%C2%A0,36751.html |title=Jesper Karlström od stycznia piłkarzem Lecha |publisher=Lech Poznań |date=2 December 2020 |accessdate=12 December 2020 |language=Polish}}</ref> In three-and-a-half-years, he totaled 144 appearances, four goals and nine assists across all competitions for Lech, won the [[2021–22 Ekstraklasa]] title and contributed to the club's best-ever European campaign in [[2022–23 Lech Poznań season|2022–23]], when they reached the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League|UEFA Europa Conference League]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jesper Karlström żegna się z Lechem |url=https://www.lechpoznan.pl/aktualnosci,2,jesper-karlstrom-zegna-sie-z-lechem,44215.html |publisher=[[Lech Poznań]] |access-date=3 August 2024 |language=pl |date=3 August 2024}}</ref>

===Udinese===
On 3 August 2024, Karlström moved to Italian club [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] on a two-year deal, for a reported fee of €2&nbsp;million with potential bonuses.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Maj |first1=Jakub |title=Lech Poznań sprzedał zawodnika. Jesper Karlström przeniósł się do Włoch. Kosta Runjaić go chciał |url=https://gol24.pl/lech-poznan-sprzedal-zawodnika-jesper-karlstrom-przeniosl-sie-do-wloch-kosta-runjaic-go-chcial/ar/c2-18718849 |website=gol24.pl |access-date=3 August 2024 |language=pl |date=3 August 2024}}</ref> He was named Udinese's captain ahead of the [[2025–26 Udinese Calcio season|2025–26 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Karlstrom new captain and Lovric vice-captain |url=https://www.udinese.it/news/squad/karlstrom-new-captain-and-lovric-vice-captain |publisher=[[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] |access-date=18 August 2025 |language=en |date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Karlström has represented Sweden at the [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|U19]] and [[Sweden national under-21 football team|U21]] levels.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Jesper Karlström – Spelarstatistik – Svensk fotboll|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/jesper-karlstrom/af4cde7e-a274-4f3e-bf95-0ab921fc1772/|access-date=2021-10-29|website=svenskfotboll.se.|language=sv|archive-date=29 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029090700/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/jesper-karlstrom/af4cde7e-a274-4f3e-bf95-0ab921fc1772/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In November 2014 he made his debut for the [[Sweden national under-21 football team]] against [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria]].<ref name="dif" />

He made his full international debut for the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] on 11 January 2018 in a [[Friendly game|friendly]] 1–0 win against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], playing for 66 minutes before being replaced by [[Kristoffer Olsson]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Sverige – Danmark – Matchfakta – Svensk fotboll|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.sehttps//www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-danmark-landskamper-herr-senior/3785289/|access-date=2021-10-29|website=svenskfotboll.sehttps|language=sv}}{{Dead link|date=March 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Karlström was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

